{
  "texts": [
    "Within this quantum computation framework, we benchmark quantum logic gates on up to three qubits and implement a hybrid variational quantum eigensolver (VQE).",
    "Benchmarking logic gates.",
    "Ideally, a gate U applied to an initial pure state |ψ⟩ will produce the pure state U |ψ⟩.",
    "In reality, errors, which are quantified by a noise channel Λ (ref.",
    "32), corrupt the final state, which is then described by a density matrix ρ = Λ(U |ψ⟩ ⟨ψ| U †)."
  ]
}